<center><font size=7><b>Sir Lancelot</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 1</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>For a lot of lives you'll
need the following program:
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;	<TABLE >
	<TR><TD WIDTH="200" BGCOLOR=gray>
<CODE>1 REM Sir Lancelot 'x' lives<BR>
10 FOR a=50000 TO 50024<BR>
20 READ n: POKE a,n: NEXT a<BR>
30 DATA 49, 125, 91, 221, 33, 128, 91, 17, 128, 36, 62, 103, 55, 205, 86, 5,243, 62, x, 50, 38, 92, 195, 8, 92<BR>
40 PRINT AT 1,3;&quot;Load Main Headerless Block&quot;<BR>
50 RANDOMIZE USR 50000
</CODE>	</TD></TR>
	</TABLE>
<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The 'x' in line 30 should be
replaced with the number&nbsp;of
lives you want - Karl tells me
that he's not sure how high you
can go but he knows that
anything up to 127 works.
Forward the tape to the main
block of code, after the
SCREEN$, run the program
and then play the tape. I'm
coming Guinevere!
 <i>(Karl Hampson in Your Spectrum issue 14)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
</table></center><P>
